rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Describes if a given file is a directory or non-directory kind of file.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: vulnerabilityExploitabilityAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a Vulnerability Exploitability eXchange (VEX) statement which provides information on whether a product is impacted by a specific vulnerability in an included package and, if affected, whether there are actions recommended to remediate. See also [NTIA VEX one-page summary](https://ntia.gov/files/ntia/publications/vex_one-page_summary.pdf).
Property describing the start time of a build.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: swhid
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SoftWare Hash IDentifier, persistent intrinsic identifiers for digital artifacts, such as files, trees (also known as directories or folders), commits, and other objects typically found in version control systems. The syntax of the identifiers is defined in the [SWHID specification](https://www.swhid.org/specification/v1.1/4.Syntax) and they typically look like `swh:1:cnt:94a9ed024d3859793618152ea559a168bbcbb5e2`.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: packagedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a packaged instance of the `from` Element (`from` packagedBy `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: email
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Email address, as defined in [RFC 3696](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc3986) Section 3.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: text
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data consists of unstructured text, such as a book, Wikipedia article (without images), or transcript.
Identifies the full text of a LicenseAddition, in SPDX templating format.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: descendantOf
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is a descendant of each `to` Element.
A collection of SPDX Elements describing a single package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sensor
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded from a physical sensor, such as a thermometer reading or biometric device.
Portion of an AnyLicenseInfo representing this version, or any later version, of the indicated License.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to related security information of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: metrics
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to metrics related to package such as OpenSSF scorecards.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: amber
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Data points in the dataset can be shared only with specific organizations and their clients on a need to know basis.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: noAssertion
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data type is not known.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: qualityAssessmentReport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a quality assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: filesystemImage

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: describes

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: support
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the artifact has been released, and is supported from the supplier. There is a validUntilDate that can provide additional information about the duration of support.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: republishedBy
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security) Designates a `from` Vulnerability's details were tracked, aggregated, and/or enriched to improve context (i.e. NVD) by each `to` Agent.
Uniquely identifies an external element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandedLicensing

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: md2

Describes a mechanism to update the dataset.
Specifies a time when a vulnerability assessment was modified

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: design
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SBOM of intended, planned software project or product with included components (some of which may not yet exist) for a new software artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: syntactic
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data describes the syntax or semantics of a language or text, such as a parse tree used for natural language processing.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: license
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional license information related to an artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: socialMedia
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a social media channel for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: expandsTo
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` archive expands out as an artifact described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasDeletedFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a file deleted from the `from` Element (`from` hasDeletedFile `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cve
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Common Vulnerabilities and Exposures identifiers, an identifier for a specific software flaw defined within the official CVE Dictionary and that conforms to the [CVE specification](https://csrc.nist.gov/glossary/term/cve_id).
Asbtract ancestor class for all VEX relationships

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: complete
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The relationship is known to be exhaustive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directory
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The file represents a directory and all content stored in that directory.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b512
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 512, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasOutputs
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Build element generates each `to` Element as an output, during a LifecycleScopeType period.

An SPDX Element containing an SPDX license expression string.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: build
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the element follows the Build profile specification
Specifies an AI package and its associated information.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityOther
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Used when there is a security related identifier of unspecified type.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: deviceDriver

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: module

Specifies the type of the external identifier.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: registration

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: graph
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is in the form of a graph where entries are somehow related to each other through edges, such a social network of friends.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: timeseries
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is recorded in an ordered sequence of timestamped entries, such as the price of a stock over the course of a day.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: application
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a software application

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: releaseHistory

Specifies the value of the content identifier.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: install

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: exploitCreatedBy

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: securityThreatModel

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: track

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sourceArtifact
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to an artifact containing the sources for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: low

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: high

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: funding

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is of a type not included in this list.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: privacyAssessment
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to a privacy assessment for a package.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: specification

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: blake2b256
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: BLAKE2b algorithm with a digest size of 256, as defined in [RFC 7693](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc7693) Section 4.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: mailingList

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is available from the additional supplier described by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasVariant
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a variant the `from` Element (`from` hasVariant `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: any hashing algorithm that does not exist in this list of entries

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: hasAddedFile
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: Every `to` Element is a file added to the `from` Element (`from` hasAddedFile `to`).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: kev
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: CISA's Known Exploited Vulnerability (KEV) Catalog

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: clickthrough
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is not publicly available and can only be accessed after affirmatively accepting terms on a clickthrough webpage.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: endOfSupport
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: there is a defined end of support for the artifact from the supplier. This may also be referred to as end of life. There is a validUntilDate that can be used to signal when support ends for the artifact.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: sha384
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: SHA-2 with a digest length of 384, as defined in [RFC 6234](https://www.rfc-editor.org/info/rfc6234).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: audio
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: data is audio based, such as a collection of music from the 80s.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: urlScheme
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) Schemes](https://www.iana.org/assignments/uri-schemes/uri-schemes.xhtml). The scheme used in order to locate a resource.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: productMetadata
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to additional product metadata such as reference within organization's product catalog.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: container
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the Element is a container image which can be used by a container runtime application

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: contains

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: development

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: medium

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: serious

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has specific context implications during an element's testing phase, during development.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element is documented by each `to` Element.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: directDownload
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: the dataset is publicly available and can be downloaded directly.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: coordinatedBy

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: generates
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: The `from` Element generates each `to` Element.
A collection of Elements that have a shared context.
A license addition that is not listed on the SPDX Exceptions List.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: cpe22
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: [Common Platform Enumeration Specification 2.2](https://cpe.mitre.org/files/cpe-specification_2.2.pdf)

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: delegatedTo

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: trainedOn

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: (Security/VEX) A `from` Vulnerability has been fixed in each of the `to` Element(s). The use of the `fixedIn` type is constrained to `VexFixedVulnAssessmentRelationship` classed relationships.

rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A reference to information assuring that the software is developed using security practices as defined by [NIST SP 800-218 Secure Software Development Framework (SSDF) Version 1.1](https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/218/final) or [CISA Secure Software Development Attestation Form](https://www.cisa.gov/resources-tools/resources/secure-software-development-attestation-form).

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: underInvestigationFor

Base domain class from which all other SPDX-3.0 domain classes derive.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: other
rdf:Description.rdfs:comment: A relationship has other specific context information necessary to capture that the above set of enumerations does not handle.

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: runtime

rdf:Description.rdfs:label: gitoid

A gitoid of type blob is a unique hash of a binary artifact. A gitoid may represent either an [Artifact Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-identifier-types) for the software artifact or an [Input Manifest Identifier](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#input-manifest-identifier) for the software artifact's associated [Artifact Input Manifest](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-input-manifest); this ambiguity exists because the Artifact Input Manifest is itself an artifact, and the gitoid of that artifact is its valid identifier. Gitoids calculated on software artifacts (Snippet, File, or Package Elements) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 SoftwareArtifact's contentIdentifier property. Gitoids calculated on the Artifact Input Manifest (Input Manifest Identifier) should be recorded in the SPDX 3.0 Element's externalIdentifier property. See [OmniBOR Specification](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/), a minimalistic specification for describing software [Artifact Dependency Graphs](https://github.com/omnibor/spec/blob/eb1ee5c961c16215eb8709b2975d193a2007a35d/spec/SPEC.md#artifact-dependency-graph-adg).

A data file can be a database file, an index file, a log file, an AI model file, a calibration data file, a temporary file, a backup file, and more. For AI training dataset, test dataset, test artifact, configuration data, build input data, and build output data, please consider using the more specific relationship types: `trainedOn`, `testedOn`, `hasTest`, `configures`, `hasInputs`, and `hasOutputs`, respectively. This relationship does not imply dependency.
